The paper discusses a framework for automated testing and vulnerability assessment in software programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of symbolic execution and machine learning also suggests a potential fit for programming languages (cs.PL), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
